    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">504.418B1/206</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 862</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-22">August 22,
                            1935</date>.<lb/>[Received September 7.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instruction No. 264 of August
                    2, 1935, directing me to ascertain the attitude of the Spanish Government toward
                    the Roerich Pact, I have the honor to report that I consulted the Foreign Office
                    and was informed that when the Spanish Government had been officially informed
                    that this Convention had been signed and ratified by all the American Republics
                    it would adhere to it.<note n="6" xml:id="d387fn6">No further communication on
                        this subject from the Spanish Government was reported by the American
                        Embassy.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Ambassador: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walter</hi> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoellkopf</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Second Secretary of Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
